         <xocs:funding-text>The analysis reported here were supported in part by a private charitable trust that wishes to remain anonymous to avoid unsolicited funding requests. The trust has had no influence on the design, analysis, interpretation and documentation of this research. The data were originally collected as part of the PhD research for Raymond Samndong supported by the Norwegian Research Council through the Man and Forest Research Project 2014–2016 , led by Prof. Arild Vatn. Projet Equateur, a program of the Woodwell Climate Research Center (previously the Woods Hole Research Center), facilitated the data collection in the DRC. The authors would like to thank the community members who generously gave their time to participate in the survey and numerous local stakeholders motivated to conserve their primary forests and natural heritage that helped to make this research project happen.</xocs:funding-text>
